quran[54]{c,v,t}:
  70,19,Surely man was created fretful
  70,20,"when evil visits him, impatient"
  70,21,"when good visits him, grudging"
  70,22,save those that pray
  70,23,and continue at their prayers
  70,24,those in whose wealth is a right known
  70,25,for the beggar and the outcast
  70,26,who confirm the Day of Doom
  70,27,and go in fear of the chastisement of their Lord
  70,28,from their Lord's chastisement none feels secure
  70,29,and guard their private parts
  70,30,"save from their wives and what their right hands own, then not being blameworthy"
  70,31,"but whoso seeks after more than that, they are the transgressors"
  70,32,and who preserve their trusts and their covenant
  70,33,and perform their witnessings
  70,34,and who observe their prayers
  70,35,"Those shall be in Gardens, high-honoured"
  70,36,"What ails the unbelievers, running with outstretched necks"
  70,37,towards thee on the right hand and on the left hand in knots
  70,38,"What, is every man of them eager to be admitted to a Garden of Bliss"
  70,39,Not so; for We have created them of what they know
  70,40,"No! I swear by the Lord of the Easts and Wests, surely We are able"
  70,41,to substitute a better than they; We shall not be outstripped
  70,42,Then leave them alone to plunge and play until they encounter that day of theirs which they are promised
  70,43,"the day they shall come forth from the tombs hastily, as if they were hurrying unto a waymark"
  70,44,"humbled their eyes, overspreading them abasement. That is the day which they were promised"
  71,1,"We sent Noah to his people, saying, 'Warn thy people, ere there come on them a painful chastisement"
  71,2,"He said, 'O my people, I am unto you a clear warner"
  71,3,"saying, \"Serve God, and fear Him, and obey you me"
  71,4,"and He will forgive you your sins, and defer you to a stated term; God's term, when it comes, cannot be deferred, did you but know"
  71,5,"He said; 'My Lord, I have called my people by night and by day"
  71,6,but my calling has only increased them in flight
  71,7,"And whenever I called them, that Thou mightest forgive them, they put their fingers in their ears, and wrapped them in their garments, and persisted, and waxed very proud"
  71,8,Then indeed I called them openly
  71,9,"then indeed I spoke publicly unto them, and I spoke unto them secretly"
  71,10,"and I said, \"Ask you forgiveness of your Lord; surely He is ever All-forgiving"
  71,11,and He will loose heaven upon you in torrents
  71,12,"and will succour you with wealth and sons, and will appoint for you gardens, and will appoint for you rivers"
  71,13,"What ails you, that you look not for majesty in God"
  71,14,seeing He created you by stages
  71,15,Have you not regarded how God created seven heavens one upon another
  71,16,and set the moon therein for a light and the sun for a lamp
  71,17,And God caused you to grow out of the earth
  71,18,"then He shall return you into it, and bring you forth"
  71,19,And God has laid the earth for you as a carpet
  71,20,"that thereof you may thread ways, ravines"
  71,21,"Noah said, 'My Lord, they have rebelled against me, and followed him whose wealth and children increase him only in loss"
  71,22,and have devised a mighty device
  71,23,"and have said, \"Do not leave your gods, and do not leave Wadd, nor Suwa', Yaghuth, Ya'uq, neither Nasr"
  71,24,And they have led many astray. Increase Thou not the evildoers save in error
  71,25,"And because of their transgressions they were drowned, and admitted into a Fire, for they found not, apart from God, any to help them"
  71,26,"And Noah said, 'My Lord, leave not upon the earth of the unbelievers even one"
  71,27,"Surely, if Thou leavest them, they will lead Thy servants astray, and will beget none but unbelieving libertines"
  71,28,"My Lord, forgive me and my parents and whosoever enters my house as a believer, and the believers, men and women alike; and do Thou not increase the evildoers save in ruin"